caption: Exceptional experience and impeccable service. I will highly recommend them.
Excellent vibe, with great music and a nice back patio.
Great selection of craft beer and a black-owned business.
Great selection of local beers (plus Michigan). Love to see a crowler option. And thanks for many nonIPA selections 👍
Seen her on Family Feud this place looks great!!

i love the fact the out door seating is in the back. it adds some privacy while still giving diners space from others. staff was attentive and food came out on time. my date and i had little to no wait time between drinks. bathrooms were well maintained and the music was bumpin haha! definitely worth it! this place is great if you're willing to try new drinks and experiment since their menu has so many delicious options to choose from.
The drinks were pre-mixed but tasty. But they also didn't have food, not even appetizers or finger foods. & who wants to drink & not eat...? They had a cool mural on the back seating area though....
Good beer choices, good bratwurst!
Great beer
This is the best place within like 50+ blocks for beer advocates to check out. It's a beer bar with harlem vibes and talented advice on what you should get drunk on :)

Love this place. I live really close and I come here all the time and it never disappoints. Good happy hour, great food, and lots of beers that change often. I hear the brunch is really good too. I'd  recommend the burger or fried chicken sandwich and definitely the fries.
Old southwestern feel. Friendly and knowledgeable host.
This place always has great customer service and has a great selection of craft beer at a fair price point. I would recommend this bar for the beer lover whose tried everything.
Went there in January and had an absolute blast. Awesome decor and great beer! Would highly recommend!

Great beer selection! Bartender was nice and friendly. Atmosphere was good, music was a little loud for midday on a Sunday but we also had a baby with us in a bar so take that with a grain of salt. Didn't try the food but we had a great time there. Will be back for the back patio in the summer!
Excellent neighborhood spot. Amazing pretzel.
Stop by during the african day parade

Really nice spot.  Good crowd.  Nice vibe.  I am not a beer connoisseur,  but I enjoyed the ones I tried.  The bar menu isn't extensive, but what they have is good.  Try the pretzels and the pretzel dog.
Nice place to drink flavored beers
Laid back, super sociable atmosphere. My first time here was like hanging out with friends I haven't spoken to in years.
This place has the beers. For real.
Love this place. Great variety of local brews and a Bavarian pretzel that is incredible and comes with three delicious dipping sauces.
(Translated by Google) #HBCU #CAU  (Original) #HBCU #CAU
Had some amazing drinks
Fabulous beer selection and great service.
Nice pub, really good beer selection

Just absurdly overpriced and music so loud that conversation was impossible. The beer wasn't good enough to warrant >= $7 for a little more than a half-pint (no beer is; it's beer). Harlem is officially bourgeois AF

(Translated by Google) The best thing I've seen in my life. Beautiful experience with my friends in Harlen. I love.  (Original) Lo mejor qwe he visto entoda mi Vida. Hermosa esperiencia con mis amistades en Harlen. Me encanta.

A very nice addition to the harlem bar scene. Their specialty is beer, to which Kevin knows all . Not to mention the vast collection of booze. Go and enjoy the drinks and the atmosphere. I will post more pics later.
Excellent bartenders that really know craft beer.
Best beer selection. Black owned beer garden. Great vibes. Must visit. I highly recommend! Own and run by HBCU alumm's!💜💜💜💜
Great beer selection.  Loved the music
Phenomenal

The service at Harlem Hops is not the warmest. This is my 3rd time in there and the first time I actually got a drink. I left both other times bc I waited at a table for longer than 30 mins and no one offered us a menu or a drink   When you walk in no one says anything to you. Not a hello or a welcome. The staff just looks at you. There's no sign that says just order at the bar. I live in the area and would love to support a local business but they make it very hard to do so.

Wonderful place to spend your hard earned money. Great beer selection and tasty bites. Music is always good and a couple of TV's to keep an eye on the game. Try and get there a little earlier than peak times to get a seat.
Great beer. Friendly service
Great craft beer and snacks, good ambiance
poor service
Nice atmosphere. Very cool vibe. Great staff.

(Translated by Google) From the moment we arrived the moment we left, we received the best and most attentive service in New York. Not to mention the quality of the products: the beers are carefully crafted and served. We will miss you until we return. To paraphrase the sign: I fell in love with Harlem Hops long before I met him.  (Original) Do momento que chegamos ao momento que fomos embora, recebemos o melhor e mais atencioso atendimento de Nova York. Isso sem contar a qualidade dos produtos: as cervejas são cuidadosamente elaboradas e servidas. Sentiremos saudade até nossa volta. Parafraseando o letreiro: eu me apaixonei pelo Harlem Hops muito antes de conhecê-lo.
Small backyard. Excellent craft beer. Good vibes. Fun atmosphere.

The DJ was Lit , the place has on there BATHROOM doors WHATEVER JUST WASH YOUR HANDS BEFORE YOU LEAVE and a chalk board in the restroom,   , but thawing i ever saw,, made me laugh so hard , the owners wife was so delightful , also the vegan sausage and pretzel bread was delicious
(Translated by Google) Super nice, and the servers are French and also super nice  (Original) Super sympa, et les serveurs sont français et aussi super sympas

I learned about this place by pure happenstance. I met one of the owners at my job and she was the absolute nicest person. I finally got a chance to stop by today and it was everything. There's an outdoor area tables that are towards the back and a very long bar. Not long enough that you'll be forgotten by the bartender but long enough that you won't overhear the conversations of people next to you. The whole place is a vibe from the dark tone of the wood to the mellow lighting...even the fixtures were just super inviting. The staff are superb and the food is even better. There were I believe 15 beers in tap and they also had wine. I would definitely  recommend this place to everyone!!!  If I could give more than five stars I would.
Best bar in Harlem! Amazing spot!
Perfect place to taste what NY has to offer. Bartenders were super knowledgable and friendly. Meet the owner and his Dad, great people serving a great product!
Great place
Great Small Batch Craft Beers.  A Harlem Jewel
Poor service

This place is dope! Great lighting, ambience and old school hip hop on a Monday night. Try it. Won't regret it. Learn your beers, sip slowly and enjoy! Thanks Josh for awesome service. Bronx in the house! Africa mother of all beers. Salud!

I live near by and have been here a couple times. Overall, the beers are really good and I like that they have the small sizes so you can try a few. The pretzel is huge! Wish they had some kind of happy hour prices. Also, love that they had music and an atmosphere going, but when they start pumping the volume it is so hard to have a conversation. My friend and I almost left because we felt like we had to scream the entire time. I even asked them to turn it down and I’m pretty sure they just pretended to do it.
Very nice and calm enviroment
Awesome atmosphere,  great food, great beer selection and awesome service!!
Hospitality..A+, Selection A+, Atmosphere A+, Decor A+, Owners and Staff AAA+. Will support always. Great establishment...BLACK OWNED A+°
Really nice neighborhood jaunt. Great selection of Brews and Wine. Food is pretty good too.
Great drinks,  nice ambiance, awesome service!!!
Great beer. Delicious food. Great service.l will be back.

I tried a lager (and a purple haze), both were excellent. But it's the vibe and ambiance that makes Harlem Hops shine. The space is clean, music is jumping, staff is on point, and the back patio is premium. I wanted to try more beers but this was our first stop on a long night. I could totally see myself chilling there for long periods of time though.
Love this place! Great little back patio, great food, great service, just great!
Great beer selection most of the time. For true beer lovers, the 10 oz, glass for $8-12 dollars need to cease.  Also, no Happy Hour is offered  which long term will negatively impact your business.
Impressive is an understatement.
Good beer. Good customer service.
Great home brewed beer fun atmosphere  and some different  aptiezer for your delight

Great place. Staff was friendly and the bites were delicious! The environment is welcoming and chill. A good variety of beer. There's adequate seating and it's definitely a place to either come with friends or sit and enjoy time alone.
Amazing spot. Great drinks and open late.

Great beer selection, clean taps, unique collection of cans..  Only one bartender will regularly treat you well...  The other seem to decide wether you get "jekle" or "hyde" with a magic 8 ball or soemthing...
Nice place COOL people come ENJOY a great beer and drinks

One of the best craft beer selections in NY. Staff is super friendly and knowledgeable about each and every item on the menu. If you are in the area this is a great place to stop and have a drink or three.
Awesome selection of beer and great food!

Harlem hops is a wonderful neighborhood bar. I love the ambiance and the music. I came in just when it opened up for the day so I scored a seat at the bar and was able to read. I wish they opened up a little earlier on a Saturday. It got crowded really fast to the point they stopped serving food. Why do you ask? Well for starters, there was only one cook in a small space next to the bar who was clearly overwhelmed. Wish I could've helped as I watched. The pies i had was good but too bad i didn't get a chance to try the sausage There was also really only one Bartender so the wait was ridiculous. He also made a mistake on my bill which I caught and saved myself $10. Overall, if you are coming for drinks, come. They have A diverse selection of beers that they change now and then.
I'm going to be honest nice place good beer food needs some love and service too
I was nice
Nice find, a pretty diverse beer selection. My favorite was the Lawson's Amber Ale. Their Bavarian pretzels are huge (cheese dip is the best). If you are in the area, definitely stop in.
So many great choices!
What an awesome spot! Black-owned, great beer, dope music, fantastic vibe!
This place is the best! The bartender was outstanding, personable and informative. Go, please go!
Top notch
Great place for craft beers, Joshua is one of the best bartenders in town. Also the security guard is such an elegant gentleman , actually one of the reasons that made me come back to the place! :)
Their beer tasting offers unique stuff. Love the set up and crowd.
Great local spot, wonderful service. Bits are tasty and filling and tend to come with crisps it banana chips..yummy

My favourite after work spot. The owners are very nice people. They are hands on and engaging. The drinks are done with love. I enjoy the bratwurst and the tiny meat pies they serve with potato and plantain chips.  One caveat, it is a pricey lil spot.
Great beer and great music.
Superb owners, great services, excellent selections...
Amazing selection of brews and excellent food — love the sausage and the giant pretzel. Gets super loud and space can be tight, so don’t go with a huge group.
Beautifully curated tap list with a great can selection as well. Great food and super friendly staff as well. Crowlers available to take your beer home with you.

(Translated by Google) Very good choice of draft beer (IPA, American Stout ...), small tapas for nibbling, American rap in the atmosphere of Harlem and broadcast NBA games. This bar is worth seeing.  (Original) Très bon choix de bière pression (IPA, Stout américaine...), petits tapas pour grignoter, rap américain dans l'ambiance de Harlem et diffusion des matchs de NBA. Ce bar vaut le détour.
Place is cool, but Fridays are the best when Julius the DJ is spinning! Awesome DJ!
The music was great. The snacks are on point. I’m brings my friends back tomorrow. Also there story is great- three teachers own it and they always keep a black brewer on tap 12.
Specialty / designer beers and wine for a mellow crowd very laid back
Awesome ambiance in this place! Awesome service, will definitely return reasonably priced beers. I loved the cider with 7.5% alchohol. They have local crafts.
Great food, amazing beer. Unexpected location. Not to miss.
The staff was super friendly, the food was good and the craft beers was amazing.😋
Such a great variety of brews, attentive service, and a nice chill vibe. More beer hall vibes than bar. I recommend!
Great vibe Great service!
Great neighborhood watering whole!
Best beer spot in Harlem!!
Cool spot! Good beer, nice vibe!
Read about this establishment and had it on our list to get to once I got to NYC.  We were not disappointed!!  Staff was very knowledgeable and friendly. We wish them much success!!
Great selection.  Friendly staff.  Try the pretzel! Really cool bar.
Really cool spot. Nice ambiance. Great selection of beers.
The premiere spot in Harlem to get the best IPA's
Nothing to complain about! Nice beers on tap, welcoming atmosphere.
Excellent service, super friendly environment. Try the Key Lime IPA by Evil Twin if you like a good sour. Cheers.
Never thought a day would come I would actually enjoy beer! Thank You Harlem Hops for opening up such a wonderful spot in our community!
Great beer selection, friendly staff, outdoor patio.

This is a cute little venue but the stools are way too high for the tables they have— my whole group left with backaches. The young lady behind the bar was completely clueless about beer, which is inconvenient while trying to select from 20 options. The crowd was a bit older, which is fine, but not what I had in mind. Their food options are limited to a giant pretzel and little empanadas, so don’t got here with a big appetite. Overall, I would go back again, but it wouldn’t be a regular spot for me.

Nice quaint place. The small bites are great. I'm a meat eater but wanted to be spontaneous and try the Vegan sausage and I promise I couldn't tell that it was meatless.  It was sooooooo tasty! Love it
Excellent beer and food, incredibly friendly people, and amazing atmosphere! Trust me, you need to go here!
Food not so good, good beer selection just requires a lot of sampling to find your favorites!
Loved this place it has a great atmosphere and the only black owned bar in Harlem. Great prices and music also!!! I'd highly recommend this place to anyone! Im coming back next time im in the city.
Harlem Hops got it right! Good drinks, good staff, good vibes! A must when in Harlem!
Good rotating drink selection and a nice vibe.
Great addition to the neighborhood, great service, intense beer selection - they have a lot here from cans to draft and outdoor space in the rear. Grab a pretzel with your beer.

The pretzel and dipping sauce are amazing! One of the owners were there when I went and she was extremely nice. Bartenders are knowledgeable of the beers and helpful wen deciding what to purchase! Reasonable prices and great atmosphere!!
Love the atmosphere and variety of options available. Can't wait to go back and bring friends with me.
awesome beer, awesome hospitality, grown & sexy crowd

Excellent beer selection. Bar tenders eager to allow tastings and explain the selection of beers. Hidden gem: the house cocktail called Purple Haze. There is a back/patio area, however it is quite close. Definitely a quieter/intimate vibe back there.

Amazing place with a great variety of beers. Josh is a outstanding bartender, very attentive and patient. I only met one of the business partners she is a smart beautiful lady.  I will definitely recommend this place to people...

As soon as I heard they'd opened up, I decided to give Harlem Hops a go because supporting black owned businesses in Harlem is a solid goal, worth the time investment. The beer choices are on point with enough variety for experimentation though it leaned IPA heavy. Not like that's a bad thing.  I feel like there should be more in the way of cider, especially with the renaissance going on in NYS and how much more accepting people who don't really care for beer would be if those options are there. Perhaps they have rotating taps and I just chose the wrong day.  There's plenty of space for sitting in the front or back which makes this spot ideal for after work shenanigans or bringing a semi-large party. I look forward to seeing how they develop as the location matures!

Great addition to the Harlem beer scene. The place has a nice feel and there's also a great outdoor patio. Interesting beer selection with a handwritten board and regularly changing beers. The bratwurst on pretzle buns are absolutely delicious. The pretzel bun was lightly toasted, the bratwurst juicy and flavorful, and the chips were the perfect accompaniment.

Harlem Hops is a true craft beer garden! The staff is amazing and they help you figure out a beer that you would like. The empanadas are delicious, especially if you like spicy food. And that pretzel? Amazing! There are positive vibes all up and through Harlem Hops! I can't wait to go back.

I really like the vibe here. BLACK owned bar in Harlem. The staff is super friendly (and fine af lol) and the crowd is cool too. The music is nice and I love their back patio. I've been here twice and I've had a great time both times. Would definitely return and recommend to folks.
Amazing huge pretzels,  best beer cheese,  nice people,  really good beer.

I know one of the owners, great guy. The place is a taste of the old Harlem and the owners are African-American so that is a change. I absolutely love this place and their devotion to good craft beer and a great environment.
Worst bartenders ever. Unprofessional and rude
Great selection of beers that match their customer service!
At least fourteen types of draft beer, including grapefruit Schofferhofer.
Great beer house with a lot of local craft beers straight on tap. Weak food selection but if you are just here for the beer highly recommend.
Great beer selection. Good experience.
Tasty, unique bar food. Welcoming service. Relaxed yet responsible security. Quality beer. Thoughtful atmosphere. And the prices are doable .
An excellent selection of beers in a well designed space with knowledgeable staff.
Great tap selection.  Great can selection (Hudson Valley cans...amazing!)  Attentive staff.  My new hangout spot.   A must visit.

Absolutely LOVED this spot & will definitely be back!!! The ambience...the music...the beer selection & I'm not a beer drinker,  but everyone with my group loved the offerings.  I had cider & even tried grapefruit beer which was different.  I'd drink it again.  Black owned wine (Brown Estates Zinfandel) which I really like is sold there as well. The food was good and the outdoor seating in the back was perfect for a Friday night out with family & friends.  I enjoyed it so much that I even bought a t-shirt which I normally don't do....no free advertising on me, but I want to support  black owned business & this one is a first for Harlem so much respect!!
Best beer selection in the city ranging from tap to cans.  Rather than trekking down to Brooklyn to get the newest Other Half releases, this will be my new go to spot.
Delicious drinks and very helpful/attentive staff
Perferct place to drink beer, great service...

I'm a huge fan of beer. I try to visit a brewhouse or two whenever I'm in a new city. In my first visit to Harlem, I stopped by this place with my best friend. I had an amazing experience. After trying a few tastes, Josh recommended a recent addition to the menu. Needless to say, the ever-changing menu leaves locals with a new experience and passersby with unique options. If you're in the city, I encourage you to go in.
This is my favorite bar now , will visit again. Friendly staff , very cozy atmosphere.

THIS PLACE IS AMAZZZZING.  I stopped by on my walk home from work and was welcomed by a variety of draft beers which included a "coffee saison." Coming into a bar alone (especially at 1:00AM) always feels a bit awkward but the staff made me feel right at home. I'm excited to come back with an appetite to have some snacks! The music was a fun mix of old and new at a perfect volume to dance or to enjoy a conversation. I will DEFINITELY be back!
Just what the neighborhood needed. I am in love with this place! The beer selection is next level.
Great to have Harlem Hops as my go to bar.   Great music, bar bites and of course, beer!

I love supporting black owned business but this one makes it really hard. I had a really bad experience and I will not be back. Hopefully as you all grow, you will get more organized and handle situations better.

Great new neighborhood spot! Very warm and welcome atmosphere with a ton of high quality craft beers on tap. The food was really tasty and I loved the bratwurst the best. Chill little back patio too. Def a good after work bar or relaxing friend weekend get together place. And even tho I can't dance the late night DJ was sick!
Hands down one of the best beer selections. Friendly and attentive staff.
Great scene, great food, and the owners are good people.
Best beer selection in the city with great music to add.
Great experience. Going to return again this Sunday.
